The paper deals with fair division, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). It also involves allocation of items, which is a problem in data structures (cs.DS). The use of an adaptive adversary and the study of fairness-efficiency tradeoffs suggest that the paper may also fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper involves probability and information theory, which are covered under cs.IT.
